{"lemma":"نافِجَةُ","slug":"نافِجَةُ","root":"ن.ف.ج","root_slug":"ن-ف-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ف-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40171"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%90%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"violence, fury","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the vehement beginning of anything","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a violently blowing wind","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a supernumerary rib","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"daughter (due to the bridewealth the father receives)","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"musk bag, the gland of the musk deer","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"musk ball, perfume flask particularly of silver or copper to store musk","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the Middle Persian ancestor of Persian نافه (nâfe)."},"ipa":["/naː.fi.d͡ʒa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40171","headword_ar":"نَافِجَةٌ","root":"nfj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencement of anything,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in two copies of the S, and so in the Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any wind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in one copy of the S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that begins with vehemence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wind that begins with vehemence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that comes with vehemence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) As thinks it to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attended by cold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AHn says, that sometimes the north wind rises upon people when they have been sleeping, and almost destroys them with cold at the close of the night, when the former part of the night has been warm: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wind that rises upon one suddenly and vehemently, when he is not aware:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAfiju","text_ar":"نَوَافِجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfijapN","text_ar":"نَافِجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cloud abounding with rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) so called from the same word as signifying “ a wind that comes with vehemence: ” (TA:) thus called by the name of the thing which is its cause. (S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfijapN","text_ar":"نَافِجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinder part of a rib:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the ribs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfijN","text_ar":"نَافِجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAfiju","text_ar":"نَوَافِجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfijapN","text_ar":"نَافِجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Camels which a man inherits, and whereby his camels are increased in number."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfijapN","text_ar":"نَافِجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A daughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because she in creases the property of her father by her dowry: (K:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that increases the property of her father:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for he takes her dowry (consisting of camels, TA) and adds it to his property, (or camels, TA,) so that the amount becomes raised. (S.) The Arabs used to say, in the time of paganism, when a daughter was born to one of them,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haniyoy^A laka Aln~aAfijapu","text_ar":"هَنِيْيا لَكَ النَّافِجَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May she who is to increase thy property by her dowry be productive of enjoyment to thee!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfijapN","text_ar":"نَافِجَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bag, follicle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vesicle, of musk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAfiju","text_ar":"نَوَافِجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) an arabicized word, (S, K,) from [the Persian]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfaho","text_ar":"نَافَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and therefore some say that it is properly written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfajapN","text_ar":"نَافَجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to the Msb, it is Arabic, and a bag of musk is so called because of its high value, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafajahu","text_ar":"نَفَجَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he magnified him, or it: ” but this requires consideration. (TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^orapu Almisoki","text_ar":"فَاْرَةُ المِسْكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^orN","text_ar":"فَاْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","A","TA","Sh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}